The paper deals with the verification of concurrent data structures, specifically concurrent priority queues. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the issue of minimizing synchronization overhead, which is a concern in programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the undecidability of verifying linearizability, which is a topic in logic and verification (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of safety-verification tools, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
